                            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">PRP results are long-lasting but not permanent because hair loss is a progressive condition. Regular maintenance sessions every 4 to 6 months help sustain results. Combining PRP with minoxidil or microneedling can extend the benefits significantly.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="post-faq-card">
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4">Does PRP for hair loss have any side effects?</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">PRP has minimal side effects since it uses your own blood. Common temporary effects include mild scalp soreness, slight swelling at injection sites, and occasional bruising. These resolve within 24 to 48 hours. There is no risk of allergic reaction or rejection.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="post-faq-card">
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4">When should I expect results from PRP for hair loss?</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Most patients notice reduced hair fall within 4 to 6 weeks of starting PRP. Visible new hair growth and thickening typically appear after 3 to 4 months. Full results are usually seen after completing the initial course of 4 to 6 sessions.</p>
